        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "James Nunez",
          "email": "james.a.nunez@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-11-20 22:55:49.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5732 hsm: sanity check for progress input",
        "message": "LU-5732 hsm: sanity check for progress input\n\nDuring an HSM archive or restore, the progress is reported by the\ncopytool, in userspace. That value may be bogus. For instance, this\nwill crash the MDS in interval_set():\n\nhe.offset = -1;\nhe.length = 10;\nrc = llapi_hsm_action_progress(hcp, &he, length, 0);\n\nSo check that userspace is giving a sane progress extent value.\n\nThis is a backport to b2_5 of\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/12285\nLustre-commit: 09974e3d70145343f10cccc8d12917814ccf2c8a\n\nSigned-off-by: frank zago <fzago@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I0eb3fa9a66400a4ff3cee2f256c08e1d84744111\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/12285\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Henri Doreau <henri.doreau@cea.fr>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n(cherry picked from commit 09974e3d70145343f10cccc8d12917814ccf2c8a)\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
  },
